description:
Leah Rous is a:

“Make-up Artist / Talent & Events Coordinator / Blogger / Newbie Stylist / Fashion Victim / Practical Fashion Finder!”

“Dream BIG. Be BRAVE. Overcome FEAR.”

I’m into fashion since I was a little girl. I love experimenting particularly when it comes to the style of my clothes, accessories, make-ups… etc. I’m a freelance makeup artist since 2007 and now I am starting to do styling as well. My fashion icons are Mary Kate and Ashley Olsen, Kate Moss, Rachel Zoe, and Gossip Girl’s Blair Waldorf. They are all classy, sophisticated, fashionable, glamorous and their styles are very fun to wear and to look at just like mine.

I’m a professional make-up artist for the past four years and worked with clients for their weddings, debuts, events, fashion shows and photo shoots. I’ve attended workshops and seminars from Maybelline and MAC Cosmetics, and worked as a marketing assistant at The Australian College of Hair Design and Beauty.

As an aspiring stylist, I want to be known as the “Stylist ng Masa”. I want the people to know that they can hire a stylist for a low price yet they can still look like a million bucks. I also wanted to show my clients that even if they don’t wear expensive branded clothes they could still look fashionably fabulous, because you don’t need to spend a lot of money just to look good.

You may also check out my other online portfolio…

Modern Archives, under the creative direction of Mae Ho, is a collection of modern silhouettes. The line was created in reaction to the mainstream trend of disposable clothing that merely followed the trends at the expense of quality and thoughtfulness. Instead Modern Archives strives for beautifully constructed clothing that accentuates one’s personal style with its subtle edginess and confidence. It’s clothing that is chic and effortless.

The line is manufactured entirely in the United States in the garment industries of Los Angeles and New York. The pieces incorporate the finest fabrics, including silk mesh, modal, and silk jersey so the pieces are not just visually but also tactilely beautiful.

Modern Archives is fashion that is simultaneously relevant and timeless.
